City of Albuquerque

************************************************************************


Your record request #25-16012 has been submitted successfully.

Greetings:

&nbsp;

The City of Albuquerque, City Clerk's Office receives 1,100-1,500 requests for public records per month and we are currently working on approximately 3,000 requests for public records, including yours.&nbsp;&nbsp;NMSA 1978 14-2-8(D).&nbsp;We will begin processing your request and will contact you if we need additional information or if your request is designated excessively burdensome and broad.&nbsp;&nbsp;



The majority of the requests we receive and process each year seek records from the Police, Planning, Fire, and Environmental Health Departments.&nbsp;A few recurring issues that arise in the course of processing requests for those departments are listed below:&nbsp;&nbsp;

* Police Department:&nbsp;* Body Worn Camera (BWC) /lapel footage is extremely time consuming for our staff to review and redact.&nbsp;

* If there are more than a few videos responsive to your request, our team will reach out to see if we can identify a more narrow set of videos in which you are interested.&nbsp;While you are not required to narrow your request, requests seeking more material take longer for us to process.



* Planning /Fire/Environmental Health Department:&nbsp;* If you are requesting records from the Planning, Fire, or Environmental Health Departments, please make sure to review City of Albuquerque Info Connect.&nbsp;

* That website may provide you with the information you are seeking regarding current development projects and other matters.





We are unable to open any links whether unsolicited, unverified, or otherwise due to the high risk of phishing, malware, or other malicious redirections. Providing information through a link does not assist us in locating incident information, if possible, please provide APD case numbers.



Our team may request a deposit for costs related to records production and data extraction prior to beginning work on your request.&nbsp;



&nbsp;To check the status of your request, or to communicate with IPRA staff, you may sign into your NextRequest account: www.nextrequest.cabq.gov.





&nbsp;

Sincerely,

&nbsp;

Ethan Watson&nbsp;

City Clerk








